A pro-Western leader of a Middle Eastern government with shaky underpinnings making unscrupulous business deals with Western corporations?  That's never happened in that region before!
<br />

<br />
Somalia and the Sudan both have oil reserves and as long they do, there will be oil companies beating down the doors of any semi-stable government that rules those nations.  Lobbyists in Washington will also push the U.S. government to ensure stability in the region so they can conduct business.  Is that a bad thing?  Not at all.  Will the respective governments of Somalia and the Sudan use any profits from the business ventures to improve their countries?  Probably not.  However, it's not the goal or responsibility of a corporation to ensure a foreign government allocates its income properly.<br />
